In article <2st9mi$5k2@nntp.ucs.ubc.ca>, 
unruh@physics.ubc.ca (William Unruh) writes:
>Could someone please send me references to the Number Field Sieve method
>of factoring? They cam e by a month or so ago, but I forgot to save
>them.
>
You could start with "The development of the number field sieve",
edited by A.K. and H.W. Lenstra, Springer lecture notes in mathematics
volume 1554, dated 1993, ISBN 0-387-57013-6.  It has chapters by the
Lenstras, Pollard, Manasse, Buhler, Pomerance, Couveignes and Bernstein,
and reprints some of the earlier articles on the subject.

Richard Pinch;  Pure Mathematics, Cambridge


